Focus on this When preparing your home for sale it can be helpful to give each room a focal point - it could be a mirror, a headboard, or a piece of furniture like the dining table. Not only does it help emphasise the purpose of the room, it can also make the space really memorable for potential buyers. It’s not just about adding furniture to an empty space. It’s how you accessorise after that gives the wow factor. A dining room table is no different. Add the crockery, add the glassware, add the napkins, add a centrepiece. Let buyers envisage themselves having dinner parties in your property. Once they see themselves living there, the deal is sealed.
